Class BruteForceMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.sri.ai.grinder.core.solver.AbstractMultiQuantifierEliminator
      • com.sri.ai.grinder.interpreter.AbstractIterativeMultiQuantifierEliminator
        • com.sri.ai.grinder.interpreter.BruteForceMultiQuantifierEliminator
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    MultiIndexQuantifierEliminator

    @Beta
public class BruteForceMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator
extends AbstractIterativeMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator
    An extension of AbstractMultiIndexQuantifierEliminator that solves quantified expressions by brute force.

    Additionally, it takes an assignment to symbols as a constructing parameter, and throws an error when a symbol with unassigned value is found.

    The reason this quantifier eliminator uses an assignment to keep a binding to variables, as opposed to using equalities in the context, is that the context can only deal with variables for which we have a satisfiability solver, whereas an assignment can be used for any variables.

    Author:
    braz
